# 2026-07-14 11:25:51.518448
+We want to modernize the codebase by achieving two main goals: making the project fully cross-platform (removing Win32 dependencies) and resolving the 53 compiler warnings.
+
+Please perform the following refactoring:
+
+    Remove Win32 Dependencies:
+
+        Replace any Win32-specific file operations (like those in Win32FileWriter or Win32FileReader) with modern, native .NET System.IO APIs (such as StreamReader, StreamWriter, File.OpenRead, etc.).
+
+        If Win32FileWriter and Win32FileReader are just wrappers, refactor them to use standard .NET cross-platform file streams, or merge/replace their usage with standard, clean FileWriter / FileReader implementations that work seamlessly on Linux, macOS, and Windows.
+
+    Fix Nullable Reference Types Warnings:
+
+        For properties in Common.cs (like Procedures, QuickStrings, InputPath, etc.) and Operator.cs (like Value, Parameters), add the required modifier (e.g., public required List<string> Procedures { get; set; }) or initialize them to default values (like  = []; or  = string.Empty;) to resolve CS8618.
+
+        For possible null references (CS8601, CS8603, CS8604), add proper null-coalescing operators (??), null-conditional access, or change target types to nullable (like string?) where appropriate (especially in Trie.cs and Common.cs).
+
+Ensure the decompiler logic remains completely unchanged, but the code compiles cleanly with zero warnings on Linux under .NET 10.

