+
+    On Linux and macOS, continue using the CLI fallback (dxbc-disassembler via Process.Start).
+
+Instructions for Core/Shaders/ShaderDecompiler.cs (and Shaders.cs):
+
+    Platform Check:
+
+        Inside the .fxc decompilation flow, check the current operating system using OperatingSystem.IsWindows().
+
+    Windows Native Path:
+
+        If running on Windows, load and call D3DDisassemble via P/Invoke to process the shader bytecode directly in memory.
+
+        Ensure we do not use any obsolete Win32 window registration or device creation. Just use the pure disassembly API.
+
+    Non-Windows Path:
+
+        If running on Linux/macOS, invoke the CLI tool dxbc-disassembler using Process.Start as we previously set up.
