+I want to transform this decompiler into a professional-grade modding tool with a full Graphical User Interface using Avalonia UI. 
+
+Please restructure the 'DecompilerGUI' to implement the following features in a clean MVVM pattern:
+
+1. Visual Layout (MainWindow.axaml):
+   - A modern, dark-themed interface.
+   - Input Section: A text field and a "Browse" button to select the game/shader folder.
+   - Output Section: A text field and a "Browse" button for the destination folder.
+   - Engine Version: A Dropdown (ComboBox) containing all the engine versions supported in 'Core/Decompiler.cs' (Vanilla, Warband, WSE2, Caribbean, etc.).
+   - Action: A large "Decompile" button.
+   - Feedback: A progress bar and a scrollable log area (TextBoard) to show real-time status messages.
+
+2. Logic Integration (MainWindowViewModel.cs):
+   - Create commands for the Browse buttons using 'StorageProvider' (Avalonia's native file picker).
+   - Link the "Decompile" button to the 'Core/Decompiler.cs' logic.
+   - IMPORTANT: Ensure the decompilation process runs on a separate Task (Thread) so the UI doesn't freeze during execution.
+   - Use 'ObservableCollection' or a similar mechanism to stream the console output from the Core directly to the GUI log area.
+
+The goal is to provide a "one-click" experience for modders. Use clean, professional English for all UI labels.
+Based in old Decomp interface: https://github.com/cuellius/decomp with modernized program

